<p>Spellcasting: as a Druid you have access to magic. You start by knowing two cantrips (of which you can cast as many times as you want) and all druid first level spells. Of the first level spells you know, you are able to cast two spells (either the same one twice, or two spells once) between each long rest. You use your wisdom modifier as your spellcasting ability. You are able to cast any spell you know with the ritual tag as a ritual (casting a spell as a ritual takes ten minutes to cast, but does not use up one of your slots.) You can use sprigs of certain plants as your spellcasting focus, but it is not required. After a long rest, you can prepare your spells, meaning that you can choose which spells you will be able to cast until the next long rest. </p>
<input type="hidden" name="spellcasting_ability" value="wis">
<input type="hidden" name="spell_save_dc" value="10">
<input type="hidden" name="spell_attack_bonus" value="2">
